# Session branch hygiene

Full SSOT: EngineerID/ambient-systems company/strategy/governance/ecosystem-branching.md

Local short form: docs/hub/branching.md

## Main safety

- Never commit or push to main. Even one-line fixes use repo/short-kebab-scope plus a PR.
- Never force-push main. Prefer small scoped PRs.

## Session close-out

1. Open or update a PR for in-session commits.
2. When CI is green and the user asked for the work: merge, confirm head deleted, prune local.
3. If abandoning: close the PR and delete the remote branch.
4. Delete orphan hub-sync or cursor heads if auto-delete missed them.
5. Prefer one open repo/* PR; do not leave ready PRs after the session.
